<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-style-center-align-caption"--><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-Mayo-Clinic-care-team-16-x-6-1024x576.jpg" alt="Mayo Clinc patient, Brady Larson and his care team who helped him celebrate with a graduation walk" class="wp-image-402869" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-Mayo-Clinic-care-team-16-x-6-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-Mayo-Clinic-care-team-16-x-6-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-Mayo-Clinic-care-team-16-x-6-768x432.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-Mayo-Clinic-care-team-16-x-6-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-Mayo-Clinic-care-team-16-x-6-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Brady Larson and his Mayo Clinic care team who organized a graduation walk</figcaption>



<p>Knowing Mayo Clinic patient Brady Larson would miss his college graduation, his Mayo Clinic care team quickly stepped in to create his own special graduation.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Brady, 20, was supposed to walk across the stage and receive his diploma at Mitchell Institute of Technology in Mitchell, South Dakota, on Friday, May 9. Instead, he was more than 300 miles away at Mayo Clinic preparing for his upcoming bone marrow transplant.</p>



<p><a href="https://youtu.be/ZTUfgyLCCLE"><strong>Watch: Graduation walk for Mayo Clinic patient, Brady Larson</strong></a></p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<div class="fluidEmbed"><iframe loading="lazy" id="videoidhttpsyoutubeZTUfgyLCCLE" title="Mayo Clinic patient, Brady Larson,  graduation walk" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZTUfgyLCCLE?feature=oembed&amp;enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div>
</div></figure>



<p></p>



<p>Determined to ensure Brady was able to celebrate the big day, his care team organized a graduation walk-through ceremony for Brady in the hospital hallway. Doctors, nurses and others cheered him on as he walked to the song "Pomp and Circumstance," clutching a graduation cap decoration and sporting a white lab coat. A celebration followed with lime green cupcakes – his school color.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Brady has severe <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/aplastic-anemia/symptoms-causes/syc-20355015">aplastic anemia</a> and needs a <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/tests-procedures/bone-marrow-transplant/about/pac-20384854">bone marrow transplan</a>t. He didn’t have to look far for a donor. His 15-year-old sister, Brooklyn, donated to help her big brother.</p>


<div class="wp-block-image is-style-center-align-caption">
<figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-family-16-x-1-1024x576.jpg" alt="Mayo Clinc patient, Brady Larson and his family" class="wp-image-402867" style="width:615px;height:auto" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-family-16-x-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-family-16-x-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-family-16-x-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-family-16-x-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/05/Brady-Larson-family-16-x-1-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Mayo Clinc patient, Brady Larson and his family</figcaption></figure></div>


<p></p>



<p>Brady graduated with a degree in agricultural business and plans to continue the family's legacy of farming in Letcher, South Dakota. <a href="https://www.nmdp.org/">Learn more</a> about becoming a bone marrow donor.</p>



